places.adr_address: Champ de Mars, 5 Av. Anatole France, 75007 Paris, France

editorial_summary.overview: Gustave Eiffel's iconic, wrought-iron 1889 tower, with steps and elevators to observation decks.

places.formatted_address: Champ de Mars, 5 Av. Anatole France, 75007 Paris, France
places.name: Eiffel Tower

reviews.text:
Visiting the Eiffel Tower was an absolute highlight of our trip, and it left us in awe of its beauty and the breathtaking views it offered. We decided to ascend to the second floor, and the experience was nothing short of magnificent. As we reached that elevation, we were greeted with a panoramic view of Paris that truly took our breath away. It's amazing how different a city can look from such a lofty vantage point. The sweeping vistas of iconic landmarks, the winding Seine River, and the sprawling cityscape were a sight to behold.

Of course, no visit to a world-famous attraction is complete without a bit of waiting, and we queued up for about an hour before we could step foot inside the tower. While the wait was a tad long, it was entirely worth it for the unforgettable experience that awaited us at the top. Plus, it gave us a chance to soak in the anticipation and excitement of the other visitors around us.

In the end, our visit to the Eiffel Tower was an absolute triumph. The memories of those astonishing views will stay with us forever, and the hour-long wait was a small price to pay for such an iconic and mesmerizing experience. If you're ever in Paris, don't miss the opportunity to ascend this legendary landmark. It's a memory you'll cherish for a lifetime.

It was such an amazing experience. We climbed to the second floor which truly wasn't bad. It was maybe 650 stairs up and there's a first floor where you can stop and get pictures. There are also gift shops, restrooms, and food stalls. Definitely get there early and buy tickets online in advance (opens 2 weeks in advance of your date) so you don't have to stand in the even longer line. The views are awesome but the experience overall is very special.

During the daytime, it isn't that much but in the evening with the lights on, it's super beautiful. We got a ticket to the second floor and it was a mesmerizing view. The stairs were a bit long but it was fine and surely worth it. The wait time was less than ten minutes when we visited at 8 p.m. on a Wednesday. As we were walking up the stairs we felt how extremely strong the wind was, the top was also closed due to the strong wind, but even though we didn't go to the top it was still beautiful and a great core memory.

At first when I saw it, nothing happened. Then I went near by and there was huge tower. Then when I went to upper side it was super view. Then in evening when I was just going on river cruise at that time it took my heart. It was so beautiful to see it skinning like gold. It is always so many people so better to get all tickets booked online. Staff was helpful however many people not know English. But overall please visit it in evening for spectacular view.

This was amazing to see! But now, when you get closer, there are lines for taking the elevator or walking up the stairs. Both have to be paid for and you have to go into a severity check point since they’ve had a bomb threat. This takes away from the spectacular structure. But there are great places to see it from afar! Especially at night when it glitters.

We didn’t have the time to go up top, plus we were traveling with a 2 year old. We were in this area for a couple of hours and I think the lines to get up would have been a couple more hours.

Buy tickets ahead of time if you want to get to the top!

places.vicinity: Champ de Mars, 5 Avenue Anatole France, Paris

places.adr_address: Pl. Charles de Gaulle, 75008 Paris, France

editorial_summary.overview: Iconic triumphal arch built to commemorate Napoleon's victories, with an observation deck.

places.formatted_address: Pl. Charles de Gaulle, 75008 Paris, France
places.name: Arc de Triomphe

reviews.text: Really cool experience, you can really spend a bit of time here reading all of the displays and material they have.  The views from the top were breathtaking and it is a don't miss spot.  It was well worth the extra ticket, it was only a few bucks more and it let us skip a line which was helpful since we were trying to zoom all around Paris in one day.

One of the most wonderful architecture in Paris signifying glory of French army.. Amazing view from top.. There is lift option for elderly but spiral stairs for regular crowd...keep water handy if planning for reaching top.

The center monument of Paris and the most famous of them all.

The monument is breath-taking and marvelous. You could purchase an online ticket for only 13€ to avoid the crowded queue on the official website.
You better chose the visit hour very carefully to avoid sun heat, I prefer sunset hour.
The stairs can be very annoying and challenging for some, especially the elders or people with special needs.
There is a souvenir store in there but most of the items and gifts are way too expensive.

The monument was closed for tours on the day we went (Monday).

Bustling intersection flanked by this impressive arch, the monument is worth exploring rather than viewing on the roadside as there’s a surprising amount to learn! One of those places you have to see in person.

Astonishing piece of architecture and historical monument!!!

To get there you should find an underground passage on the sidewalk near the main road. There is a line if you want to purchase a ticket to climb the arc. If you don't want to climb..bypass the line and simply go to the main quad area to see and experience the arc from upclose in the ground.

editorial_summary.overview: Former historic palace housing huge art collection, from Roman sculptures to da Vinci's "Mona Lisa."

reviews.text: It's as amazing as it looks on TV, movies, etc. And then some. Priceless works of art adorn each hall, staircase, etc. It's crowded, but not overwhelming. Everyone should visit here at least once in their lifetime and see for themselves.

Absolutely stunning museum with some of the most stunning masterpieces in the world! The building itself is also a work of art, you have to remember to look up when admire the ceilings - paintings and mouldings throughout.

We got a group tour skip-the-line tickets direct from the Louvre. After the tour we spent the rest of the day to see Michelangelo statues, French paintings and the Egyptian exhibit. It’s well worth your time!

Would recommend a guide and buying tickets ahead. Enjoy!

Lots to see in the museum. I would recommend buying your ticket online ahead of time so you can skip the long queue. If you want to see all of the exhibits, you should spend at least half a day. If you visit in the morning when they open, I suggest you go straight to the Mona Lisa painting, and then visit the rest of the exhibits. Definitely worth the visit!

We purchased our tickets online (apparently people under 25, EU citizens get tickets free of charge) and joined the queue 15 minutes before our slot. Even though the queue was quite long, it went very quick. Great organization!

Once inside, everything is well organized with information desks and the opportunity to get yourself some Nintendo guides. I have never seen such amazing guides and you just got to pay 5€ (no need to order in advance).
This device always knows your location and will give you information about the art based where you are located. Absolutely incredible!

The louvre itself, the building, the rooms, are absolutely amazing. I have no words for the beauty and the size of it. We have totally underestimated the time we would spend in the louvre.

We arrived at 12 and started right at the 2nd floor as it was less busy. I guess everyone starts at the bottom first and gets tired by the time walking up? In any case, I would recommend at least (!!!) 3 hours.

This must have been the most amazing museum I have been to. I absolutely loved it - 100/10.

Unbelievable collection of art, statues and everything!  You could spend an entire day here easily!  We did a guided tour, which I would recommend.  Take the early tour so you can just walk around after the guided tour!

places.adr_address: 1 Shi Ji Da Dao, Lujiazui, Pu Dong Xin Qu, Shang Hai Shi, China, 200120

editorial_summary.overview: Futuristic TV tower (468-meters tall) offering city vistas, a history museum & revolving restaurant.

places.formatted_address: 1 Shi Ji Da Dao, Lujiazui, Pu Dong Xin Qu, Shang Hai Shi, China, 200120
places.name: Oriental Pearl TV Tower

reviews.text: The Oriental Pearl TV Tower in Shanghai offers breathtaking views, but my visit during the weekend was less than ideal. The crowd was overwhelming, and I endured a nearly 3-hour wait in the queue. Once I finally reached the observatory, my mood was dampened, and I only spent a quick 15 minutes taking in the view before heading down. I strongly recommend planning your visit during off-peak hours to fully enjoy this iconic attraction without the frustration of overcrowding.
Nothing too special here. Glass floor, old Shanghai museum, good view. Skip going to the highest level with the space exhibit and tiny viewing windows. Get there early.
If you look to Shanghai from this tower, it's just normal view city at night, but look from the other side to this. It generous! Busy street at night, don't have a chance to go to the top!
A little bit expensive entrance fee, but worthy to visit this observatory. Able to get cheaper tickets if you book earlier.
Amazing lightshow at 19:00 when the light goes on. In weekend very busy near the bund and tower. Enjoy the view.

places.vicinity: 1 Shi Ji Da Dao, Pu Dong Xin Qu

places.adr_address: 2000 Shi Ji Da Dao, Pu Dong Xin Qu, Shang Hai Shi, China, 201204

editorial_summary.overview: Modern museum focusing on technology, with educational programs, multimedia exhibits & theaters.

places.formatted_address: 2000 Shi Ji Da Dao, Pu Dong Xin Qu, Shang Hai Shi, China, 201204
places.name: Shanghai Science and Technology Museum

reviews.text: This place is absolutely great. Definitely a landmark to visit on a school field trip. It is very educational and provides many resources for those that want to learn about science and technology. So many convenient things as well. Not to mention the portable charging stations all around. Come and check it out. It will not disappoint.

Shopping is all underground adjacent to the subway station entrance. Be prepared for locals trying to steer you towards particular shops and be very very pushy. Some deals are to be had but be prepared to negotiate.

If you like the technology and scientist, this place is good for you. Better come to this place with your children coz it was fun with them. They can learn scientist on this place. The most museum i like was the zoology section. I like the animal zone from around the world and the tropical forest.

The Shanghai Science & Technology Museum is a great place to take the kids. It is huge - 4 floors, several exhibition hall, and several IMAX/IWERKS theatres.

We arrived soon after it opened and stayed until late afternoon. The kids had a great time in the robot and space areas, and the younger ones enjoyed the wildlife exhibitions.

It’s easy to get to on the Metro and has its own stop on Line 2.

Outside of museum is with ample space, can book tickets online also. Direct exit from subway station. Close to the museum, there's a big shopping area. Prices are bit higher than normal, but always need to bargain. It's fun to shopping there...but do not buy unless you accept the price is right.

places.vicinity: 2000 Shi Ji Da Dao, Pu Dong Xin Qu

places.adr_address: 105 Namsangongwon-gil, Yongsan-gu, Seoul, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Opened in 1980, this iconic tower offers panoramic views of the city & a revolving restaurant.

places.name: N Seoul Tower

reviews.text: Such an incredible place to visit. The views of Seoul from the top of tower are amazing. We got the couples package that included tickets to the tower, a heart lock to attach to the love lock fence, and 2 drinks at the top of the tower. It was definitely worth it. I highly recommend taking the cable car to the tower too. It was an awesome way to take in the views on the way up.

Somebody said to me that "N Seoul Tower is never disappointing," and they were right! I absolutely loved my visit today and can't wait to go back. The tower itself is very impressive and offers a great view of the city. The surrounding area also offers many spots for observation and photos. The walk/hike up the mountain looks like it would be very enjoyable. You just need the correct shoes as there are lots of steps and inclines involved. I used the cable car on my visit, which offered lovely views. A must-see for anyone visiting Seoul.

The tower was wonderful and offered great views of Seoul. We took the Namsam Cable Car to the tower, but you can also take stairs if you would prefer to walk. There are cafes and food options in and around the tower. We didn't try any of those. There are also music and performances on the grounds of the tower which were enjoyable to watch. I suggest coming first thing in the morning when it opens, which is what we did. It got very busy by the afternoon. This is a must do tourist attraction!

Great place to visit in Seoul. So much more to this place than just a tall tower. Good (touristy) shops and plenty of quality places to eat. The views, as expected, is fantastic. But the best part for us was the martial arts show, which we caught just by chance. Must see!!!

Fantastic view of Seoul. Nice place. It's worth visiting both during the day and at night. Have to wait for the cable car on weekdays, as well as on the way back. Restaurants, cafes, shops, bar, entertainment area, gallery, many things can be found.

places.adr_address: 16 Itaewon-ro 26-gil, Yongsan-gu, Seoul 04391, South Korea
places.name: ITAEWON

reviews.text: Food selection here is pretty good. Access to Itaewon is easy by public transit. If you’re a fan of “that” show, it’s a must.
Food is good but not great but again you come here to have a great time. It starts off slow in the beginning of the night, but progress to be an amazing environment

We were deeply saddened to learn about the tragic events that took place in Itaewon during Halloween in 2022. Our hearts go out to the families and friends who have been affected by this devastating incident. While exploring the area, we unexpectedly came across a place where it seemed that those impacted by the tragedy had left their final messages.

It was a poignant and somber reminder of the lives that were lost and the profound impact it had on the community. We join in hoping that the victims find peace, and our thoughts are with their loved ones.
Past and present... Antiquity decor from 1960's and 70's. Netflix Kdrama Itaewon Class was filmed here.
Fun city in korea .we have lot of fun in this city .every kind of people have thair

place.name: Rome

places.adr_address: Piazza del Colosseo, 1, 00184 Roma RM, Italy

editorial_summary.overview: Monumental 3-tiered Roman amphitheater once used for gladiatorial games, with guided tour option.

places.formatted_address: Piazza del Colosseo, 1, 00184 Roma RM, Italy
places.name: Colosseum

plus_code.compound_code: VFRR+3V Rome, Metropolitan City of Rome Capital, Italy

reviews.text:
What an awe-inspiring structure and historical location. We entered the Roman Forum and walked the “gladiators road” to The Colosseum. You can take a guided tour or walk through on your own, but either way, purchase tickets through the website in advance. We did enjoy having a guide who was knowledgeable about The Colosseum’s history and could explain many of the structural and historical pieces or answer questions. The entrance and ticket sales are limited, but it is still quite crowded inside, but there is also plenty of space through our space, and no one was rude during our experience. You can also walk around the outside and take in the view and surrounding monuments.

If you are in Rome, this is a must-see, and I would suggest a walk through the Roman Forum as well. You really feel immersed in Roman history.

Parking/Location: I am not sure of parking as we did not drive to the area, but there is a Metro and public transportation in the area. It is also walkable from the Roman Forum and other destinations in the area.

If you find this helpful, please click the 👍 below and follow me for more.

You absolutely have to go here. I'd suggest ordering the tickets online a day or two in advance and just going your own slow guided tour.  After that you can check our YouTube and find some real nice virtual tours you can do that night.  Highly recommend. Also consider the Roman forum as well as watching the gladiator movie which is very satisfying as usual lol

If you are at all interested in the history of the "old world" then this is the place to visit. Incredible piece of an ancient world that existed a very long time ago.  Thank you Italy for preserving clues to such a remarkable civilization. We paid for a tour so we didn't have to wait in the lines to get into these places, they were very busy even at the end of the season.

Absolutely mesmerizing.. a part of history comes alive at this place.

Visiting the Colosseum, was actually living , seeing and experiencing the texts books and history attached to it. Thus so far, I had only read and heard about this iconic structure , however seeing it with my eyes was something entirely different and awe- inspiring.

We had a guide as we had to scrounge for last minute tickets, and I have to admit, the guide we had was a professor in architectural history, retelling the history as it unfolded with immense knowledge, precision and passion. His expertise rendered the entire experience even more valuable and interesting than it already was..:) and were we not glad!!!

The place is very very busy with hordes of crowd, nevertheless very well- managed. The beauty of the structure is that even on an extremely hot August afternoon( we entered the Colosseum at 2 pm) the place is very well ventilated. Such was the mastery in the creation and construction of this building.

Most of all, we visited both during the day and night . At night, the building looks stunning and worth a visit..an absolute must when in Roma.

I definitely would like to add that Roma is not , not , not , not unsafe. They have their special force in service everywhere, protecting , guiding and taking care for the citizenry and tourists. It’s a wonderful place to visit and once in a life time experiences
Absolutely, by far, one of my all time favorite places to visit. So much history and little known facts were given. We did a tour with a fantastic Italian guide. The tour was 5 hours and perfect.

places.adr_address: Piazza della Rotonda, 00186 Roma RM, Italy

editorial_summary.overview: Iconic temple built circa 118 to 125 A.D. with a dome & Renaissance tombs, including Raphael's.

places.formatted_address: Piazza della Rotonda, 00186 Roma RM, Italy
places.name: Pantheon

plus_code.compound_code: VFXG+CP Rome, Metropolitan City of Rome Capital, Italy

reviews.text:
There aren’t many structures in the world
with more history than the Pantheon. It you plan to visit do yourself a favor and read up on the history of this sacred place. It is full of marvel. Its history and use is very interesting. It has been used in many ways and today it is an active Catholic church and parish. We attended mass on a Saturday afternoon to conclude our visit. It was a fitting way to conclude our day and highly recommend it. The mass was in Italian with a couple of the readings in English.
The architectural aspect of the Pantheon is amazing and again read all about it first and then when you visit you will enjoy it more.
There are a few people buried here as well. The first 2 presidents of Italy and artist Raphael. Their stories are very interesting and especially how Keats ended up being buried here. If you love history as I do and you visit Italy do not miss the Pantheon. The square and area around it are vibrant and have numerous restaurants and shops to visit.

The Pantheon is amazing! Built 2,000 years ago, it's a giant dome with a hole in the top. Inside, it's peaceful and awe-inspiring. The ancient architecture is jaw-dropping. A must-visit in Rome, showcasing the brilliance of the past. Don't miss this historical marvel!" Entry ticket was 5 euros

Incredible ancient Roman Temple that has since been converted to yet another Catholic church. Best to do a guided tour so you can learn so much more than what you can learn otherwise. After doing the inside, walk the entire perimeter of the outside to get an even greater appreciation of the skill that went into the construction of this immense structure.

Good place to stop by and check out the architecture and history of the pantheon. Interesting dome design.
Not very big compared to other sites but it is a good place to visit. Also very busy and long queues if you don't get a ticket online.

One of Rome's iconic sites, need to visit. Our visit was mid afternoon on a Thursday. Was mildly busy in comparison to other sites. Decided last second to go in, waited less than 30 min to get in. The Piazza was not excessively crowded either. Enjoy!

editorial_summary.overview: Catholic city-state & home of the Pope, known for Sistine Chapel frescoes & St. Peter’s Basilica.
